                            <comment id="13285080" author="teofili" created="Tue, 29 May 2012 20:16:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;IMHO this should be fixed, especially with SolrCloud (and collection management API, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-3488&quot; title=&quot;Create a Collections API for SolrCloud&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-3488&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-3488&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) coming the described situation is likely to happen more frequently.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13285435" author="teofili" created="Wed, 30 May 2012 06:50:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I just tested this doesn&apos;t apply to Solr 4 thus I think this issue can be marked as resolved with Fix Version 4.0.&lt;br/&gt;
Sebastian, can you also check if your scenario works with Solr 4?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13287697" author="tomasflobbe" created="Fri, 1 Jun 2012 21:41:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I checked this and saw the same as Tommaso, it seems to work on trunk and 4x branch. &lt;br/&gt;
I added a test case that start the CoreContainer with no cores (a solr.xml file with an empty list of cores). It works on trunk and fails on 3.6 with an exception as the one described in the description of this issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13288419" author="teofili" created="Mon, 4 Jun 2012 08:35:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;thanks Tom&#225;s, your patch looks good. I&apos;ll mark this as resolved in version 4.0&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13401227" author="mange" created="Tue, 26 Jun 2012 07:56:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This still needs to be fixed for 3.6. We don&apos;t want to start running trunk in production here.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13401231" author="mange" created="Tue, 26 Jun 2012 08:06:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bug was introduced by SVN commit 1211850 in relation to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-1730&quot; title=&quot;Solr fails to start if QueryElevationComponent config is missing&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-1730&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-1730&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. Seems like just reverting that commit would fix the problem.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13401469" author="janhoy" created="Tue, 26 Jun 2012 15:54:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Updated 3.6 patch which simply removes the zero cores check/throw - this mirrors current trunk/4.0 code.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
